#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.116"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.116:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.116:0.2"
msgid "12. Āpāyikavagga "
msgstr "12. Bound for Loss "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.116:0.3"
msgid "116. Āneñjasutta "
msgstr "116. Imperturbable "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.267, sc1
msgctxt "an3.116:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these three people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an3.116:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo? "
msgstr "What three? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.116:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "First, a person, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "an3.116:1.4"
msgid "So tadassādeti taṃ nikāmeti tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati, tatra ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno ākāsānañcāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying. If they’re set on that, committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the dimension of infinite space. "

msgctxt "an3.116:1.5"
msgid "Ākāsānañcāyatanūpagānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ vīsati kappasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "The lifespan of the gods of infinite space is twenty thousand eons. "

msgctxt "an3.116:1.6"
msgid "Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati. "
msgstr "An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm. "

msgctxt "an3.116:1.7"
msgid "Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati. "
msgstr "But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life. "

msgctxt "an3.116:1.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person as regards their place of rebirth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.268, sc2
msgctxt "an3.116:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a person, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the dimension of infinite consciousness. "

msgctxt "an3.116:2.2"
msgid "So tadassādeti taṃ nikāmeti tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati, tatra ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno viññāṇañcāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying. If they’re set on that, committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the dimension of infinite consciousness. "

msgctxt "an3.116:2.3"
msgid "Viññāṇañcāyatanūpagānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ cattārīsaṃ kappasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "The lifespan of the gods of infinite consciousness is forty thousand eons. "

msgctxt "an3.116:2.4"
msgid "Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati. "
msgstr "An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm. "

msgctxt "an3.116:2.5"
msgid "Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati. "
msgstr "But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life. "

msgctxt "an3.116:2.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person as regards their place of rebirth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.116:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a person, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "an3.116:3.2"
msgid "So tadassādeti taṃ nikāmeti tena ca vittiṃ āpajjati, tatra ṭhito tadadhimutto tabbahulavihārī aparihīno kālaṃ kurumāno ākiñcaññāyatanūpagānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "They enjoy it and like it and find it satisfying. If they’re set on that, committed to it, and meditate on it often without losing it, when they die they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the dimension of nothingness. "

msgctxt "an3.116:3.3"
msgid "Ākiñcaññāyatanūpagānaṃ, bhikkhave, devānaṃ saṭṭhi kappasahassāni āyuppamāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "The lifespan of the gods of nothingness is sixty thousand eons. "

msgctxt "an3.116:3.4"
msgid "Tattha puthujjano yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā nirayampi gacchati tiracchānayonimpi gacchati pettivisayampi gacchati. "
msgstr "An ordinary person stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they go to hell or the animal realm or the ghost realm. "

msgctxt "an3.116:3.5"
msgid "Bhagavato pana sāvako tattha yāvatāyukaṃ ṭhatvā yāvatakaṃ tesaṃ devānaṃ āyuppamāṇaṃ taṃ sabbaṃ khepetvā tasmiṃyeva bhave parinibbāyati. "
msgstr "But a disciple of the Buddha stays there until the lifespan of those gods is spent, then they’re extinguished in that very life. "

msgctxt "an3.116:3.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso, ayaṃ adhippayāso idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanena, yadidaṃ gatiyā upapattiyā. "
msgstr "This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person as regards their place of rebirth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.116:3.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.116:3.8"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

